Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[dscrd-hush] <ComputerGenie - ChickenPool> Not that it should be taking up HUSH real estate, but:
LABS main value comes from its being an "ecosystem within an ecosystem" and it's the value payment coin for those that notarize LABS ecosystem chains (among other things).
It's not a "test coin"; think of a KMD ecosystem inside the KMD ecosystem and it would be the equivalent of the internal KMD, but since it has its own dev team and pace, it's kind of a bad analogy but hopefully enough to paint the picture.
Much of the work done in LABS has already produced a better komodod and iguana (as well as it being the place where staking inside the Komodo ecosystem began and survived testing).
Why would anyone want to buy any currency?
It's a 51:49 staking:mining chain so ASICs cannot over-run stakers, ever.
